- **Add Spring Boot Caching Dependency**:
  ```xml
  <dependency>
      <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
      <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-cache</artifactId>
  </dependency>
  ```

- **Enable Caching in Application**:
  ```java
  @SpringBootApplication
  @EnableCaching
  public class MyApplication {
      public static void main(String[] args) {
          SpringApplication.run(MyApplication.class, args);
      }
  }
  ```

- **Configure Cache Manager (e.g., Redis)**:
  ```yaml
  spring:
    cache:
      type: redis
      redis:
        host: localhost
        port: 6379
  ```

- **Use @Cacheable Annotation**:
  ```java
  @Service
  public class MyService {
      @Cacheable("myCache")
      public String getCachedData(String key) {
          // Expensive operation
          return "Cached Data";
      }
  }
  ```

- **Configure Cache Expiration**:
  ```yaml
  spring:
    cache:
      redis:
        time-to-live: 3600s
  ```

- **Use @CachePut Annotation for Updates**:
  ```java
  @Service
  public class MyService {
      @CachePut(value = "myCache", key = "#key")
      public String updateCachedData(String key, String value) {
          return value;
      }
  }
  ```

- **Use @CacheEvict Annotation for Removals**:
  ```java
  @Service
  public class MyService {
      @CacheEvict(value = "myCache", key = "#key")
      public void removeCachedData(String key) {
          // Logic to remove data
      }
  }
  ```

- **Supported Cache Types**:
  - `simple`: In-memory cache.
  - `caffeine`: High-performance in-memory cache.
  - `redis`: Distributed cache using Redis.

- **Latest Version of Spring Boot Caching**:
  Check [Maven Central](https://search.maven.org/artifact/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-starter-cache) for the latest version.
